description.narrative: EAPRO continued to support governments and communities to control the spread of the virus and minimize morbidity and mortality, including by enhancing preparedness for the possible new waves of COVID-19 in 2021 and addressed the socio-economic impacts of the pandemic in the region by restoring children’s mental and physical well-being in the areas of health, nutrition, WASH, child protection, education and social protection, focusing on the most vulnerable.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/03/2022
